{"word":"G2699 - κατατομή - katatomḗ - kat-at-om-ay' - Concision","slug":"G2699","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<strong>Original: </strong><span class=\"hebrewOrGreek\">κατατομή</span>"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Transliteration: </strong>katatomḗ"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Phonetic: </strong>kat-at-om-ay'"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Short Definition: </strong>Concision"},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<b>&#x03BA;&#x03B1;&#x03C4;&#x03B1;&#x03C4;&#x03BF;&#x03BC;&#x03B7;&#x0301; - katatome&#x0304;</b> - <i>kat-at-om-ay'</i><p/>From a compound of <a href=\"#/G2596\">G2596</a> and <b>&#x03C4;&#x03B5;&#x0301;&#x03BC;&#x03BD;&#x03C9;</b> <b>temno&#x0304;</b> (to <i>cut</i>); a <i>cutting down</i> (<i>off</i>), that is, <i>mutilation</i> (ironically): - concision. Compare <a href=\"#/G609\">G609</a>."},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<strong>Cognate:</strong> <a href=\"#/G3718\">G3718</a>, <a href=\"#/G663\">G663</a>, <a href=\"#/G664\">G664</a>"}]}